LOGISTIC REGRESSION 
- y {-1,1} is a state on Boltzmann distribution conditioned on the input of x^ (augmented features, length is m+1)
- Every state y has an energy (E(y,x^) and an inverse temperature (Beta) which are used to build the probability
        P(y | x^) =     [ exp (-BE(y,x^))]  /   [SUM (exp (-BE(y,x^)))]
        - in binary -1,1 case, the sum function is possible to calculate and the probability can be calculated 
        - large beta means probability distribution is sharper
            B --> infinity , sharper distribution, temperature is going down, (frozen state, no movement and no uncertainty)
            B --> 0 , maximum uncertainty, means system is REALLY hot (1/T) 
            B = 1 is a baseline balance between uncer
        - Energy(y,x^) = - y(x^theta) 
            energy for y = +1 is high 
            energy for y = -1 is low 
